 <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
  <subfield code="a">Decaying steady states of the one-dimensional nonlinear Schrödinger equation with a constant potential</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">IOP</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
  <subfield code="a">We introduce a set of non-linear functions of real, exponential type that can be useful for dealing with some physical problems. We use these functions to find steady states of the one-dimensional non-linear Schrödinger equation for a condensate between an infinite barrier and a step potential in the case where the height of the step is larger than the chemical potential of the condensate.</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">IOP</subfield>
 </datafield>
